	<item>
		<title>Weekend Project: Opening Title Sequence</title>
		<link>http://www.knanthony.com/blog/weekend-project-opening-titles/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 26 Sep 2014 14:53:30 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[anthkris09]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.knanthony.com/blog/?p=26</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I like to spend the weekends figuring out neat tricks, learning new skills, and creating cool projects. Yes, I have no life.

So, I stumbled on this recut of Mary Poppins as a horror film several years ago and I loved it. It's really good and funny, too.

[embed]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2T5_0AGdFic[/embed]

And, much more recently, I stumbled upon this great tutorial on <a class="postlink" title="Text Opening Sequence" href="http://tympanus.net/codrops/2013/04/30/text-opening-sequence-with-css-animations/" target="_blank">creating an opening title sequence using CSS animations from CodeDrops.</a> I bookmarked it and forgot about it. But when I rediscovered it, I really wanted to do something with it. So I did!

I created a trailer using the CSS animations, based on the Scary Mary video (plus I created a GIF from <a class="postlink" title="Moon and Clouds Timelapse" href="https://archive.org/details/MoonAndCloudsTimeLapse2" target="_blank">this Moon and Clouds timelapse</a> and added music: <a class="postlink" title="Incomptech Royalty Free Music" href="http://incompetech.com/music/royalty-free/index.html?isrc=USUAN1100574" target="_blank">Awkward Meeting from Kevin McLeod</a>)

<a class="postlink" title="Scary Mary Opening Sequence" href="http://www.knanthony.com/showcase/opening-sequence/index.html" target="_blank">Check out the final trailer here.</a>

<a href="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/scary-mary.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-28 size-large" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/scary-mary-1024x571.png" alt="scary mary css title sequence trailer" width="550" height="306" /></a>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
