	<item>
		<title>ELH Challenge: My Favorite Freelancing Tip</title>
		<link>http://www.knanthony.com/blog/elh-challenge-my-favorite-freelancing-tip/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 02 Dec 2014 21:21:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[anthkris09]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.knanthony.com/?p=277</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[I am not a freelancer.

But I've thought about it a lot; what it would mean and how it might fit into my life now. I'm really happy with my current position but I do often take work home so the whole thought of keeping time to recharge along with regular work and freelancing work is overwhelming. Besides which, though I don't believe I'm a perfectionist, I do really appreciate the time and space to practice on all the aspects of design because I'm always looking to get better.<!--more-->

So that's why the first tip from <a class="postlink" title="20 Pro Tips for Web Design Freelancers" href="http://www.creativebloq.com/netmag/20-pro-tips-web-design-freelancers-4145555" target="_blank">CreativeBloq's 20 Pro Tips for Web Design Freelancers</a> really struck me:
<blockquote>Be amazing at something.</blockquote>
Though I may never be the best at anything, that never stops me from trying. I really like to be able to know, whenever I go into an interview situation, that I'm not just some mediocre instructional designer. I'm damn good and I'm working to get better. So for this week's Elearning Heroes Challenge, I posterized this great tip using a free Photoshop poster mockup. 'Cause, hey, I don't do boring.

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-278" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/favoritefreelancertip.png" alt="Favorite Free Lancing Tip" width="700" height="670" />]]></content:encoded>
