			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[Failing can indeed be part of the fun, since mastering something is a rush.  The trick seems to be to keep the feedback loop short and keep the punishment light.  That ties into the "frequent save points" thought, but I'd push a bit further and say that far too many games think that punishing the player is more important than teaching the player and letting them win.  There's almost an ego contest between designer and player, in some ways, but I think that too many designers want to beat the players.  It's hard sometimes, but as a designer, you need to let the player win.

