		<title>What I did This Weekend</title>
		<link>http://www.knanthony.com/blog/what-i-did-this-weekend/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2015 14:11:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[anthkris09]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.knanthony.com/?p=1037</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[column_one_half]

I declared <a title="Consistency: Key to Creativity" href="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/consistency-key-to-creativity/">2015 my Year of the Project.</a> So far, this has served me exceedingly well. Just about every week, I've either completed a smallproject or worked towards a larger project. It's been fun, informative, and it's helped me build my skills. I'm looking forward to continuing to improve the rest of the year. But I've noticed that, perhaps especially when you enjoy the work, it's really really easy to edge ever closer towards burnout.

[/column_one_half]

[column_one_half_last]

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1033" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0394-1024x768.png" alt="IMG_0394.PNG" width="605" height="454" />

[/column_one_half_last]

<!--more-->

[column_one_half]

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1032" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0393-1024x768.png" alt="IMG_0393.PNG" width="605" height="454" />

[/column_one_half]

[column_one_half_last]

So this weekend, I didn't do <strong><em>Anything.</em></strong>

[/column_one_half_last]

[column_one_half]

Which, for me, means playing video games.

[/column_one_half]

[column_one_half_last]

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1030" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0395-1024x768.png" alt="IMG_0395.PNG" width="605" height="454" />

[/column_one_half_last]

&nbsp;

[column_one_half]

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1045" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0396-1024x768.png" alt="IMG_0396.PNG" width="605" height="454" />

[/column_one_half]

[column_one_half_last]

I definitely felt a bit guilty for not working on something.

[/column_one_half_last]

[column_one_half]

But the bottom line is, sometimes, I need the time off.

[/column_one_half]

[column_one_half_last]

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1034" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0397-1024x768.png" alt="IMG_0397.PNG" width="605" height="454" />

[/column_one_half_last]

&nbsp;

[column_one_half]

So I can come back stronger to everything I do.

[/column_one_half]

[column_one_half_last]

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1031" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0392-1024x768.png" alt="IMG_0392.PNG" width="605" height="454" />

[/column_one_half_last]

[column_one_half]

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1036" src="http://www.knanthony.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0398-1024x768.png" alt="IMG_0398.PNG" width="605" height="454" />

[/column_one_half]

[column_one_half_last]

And that's worth not getting work done every once in a while.

[/column_one_half_last]]]></content:encoded>
