			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[Hi Kristin, I got the ping back to my post and found your comments quite interesting. One thing I've been thinking about since writing that post is the temporal quality of innovation. How does time effect "innovation"? At present I'm actually leaning towards an idea that you can't really say it's an innovation until there's been change. It's almost as if innovation is a term that can really only be applied retrospectively. It's completely at odds with current usage of the term, but I think it's an interesting way of framing it.

